ezvcard.property

Class SortString

  • java.lang.Object
    • ezvcard.property.VCardProperty
      • ezvcard.property.SimpleProperty<String>
        • ezvcard.property.TextProperty
          • ezvcard.property.SortString
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparable<VCardProperty>

    public class SortString
extends TextProperty

    Defines the string that should be used when an application sorts this vCard in some way.

    This property is not supported in 4.0. Instead, use the StructuredName.setSortAs(java.lang.String) and/or Organization.setSortAs(java.lang.String...) methods when creating version 4.0 vCards.

    Code sample (vCard versions 2.1, 3.0) 

     VCard vcard = new VCard();
 
 StructuredName n = new StructuredName();
 n.setFamily("d'Armour");
 n.setGiven("Miles");
 vcard.setStructuredName(n);
 SortString sortString = new SortString("Armour");
 vcard.setSortString(sortString);

    Code sample (4.0) 

     VCard vcard = new VCard();
 
 StructuredName n = new StructuredName();
 n.setFamily("d'Armour");
 n.setGiven("Miles");
 n.setSortAs("Armour");
 vcard.setStructuredName(n);

    Property name: SORT-STRING

    Supported versions: 2.1, 3.0

    Author:
    Michael Angstadt
